- Intent-driven development: Focus on what you want, not how to code it
- AI as execution partner: AI writes and debugs code based on your descriptions
- Outcome-first thinking: Start with the end result and work backward
- Iterative refinement: Build, test, improve in rapid cycles
- Human-AI collaboration: You provide direction, AI provides implementation

## Real-World Example
Imagine you want to build a simple to-do app. In traditional coding, you would spend weeks learning HTML, CSS, JavaScript, then frameworks, then databases. With Vibe Coding, you open a tool like Bolt.new or Lovable, describe ''I want a to-do app where users can add tasks, mark them complete, and delete them,'' and within minutes you have a working prototype. You refine it by saying ''make the completed tasks gray and move them to the bottom,'' and the AI updates the code instantly.

## Practical Application
By the end of this course, you will be able to describe a software idea in plain English and use AI tools to build it into a working application. You will understand which tools to use for different types of projects, how to give effective instructions to AI, and how to iterate on your builds until they match your vision.

