('10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000004', '10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002', 'AI-First Development Workflow', 'Understanding tools is important, but knowing how to use them together in an effective workflow is what separates productive Vibe Coders from those who struggle. This lesson teaches you the AI-First development workflow—a systematic approach to building software with AI tools.

The AI-First development workflow follows a clear pattern: Describe, Generate, Evaluate, Refine, Deploy. You start by describing what you want in plain language, then generate code or an application using AI tools. You evaluate the output against your requirements, refine through iterative prompting, and finally deploy to production. This cycle can happen many times per day, enabling rapid iteration that was impossible with traditional development.

Without a structured workflow, Vibe Coding can feel chaotic. You might waste time regenerating the same code, lose track of what you''ve tried, or get stuck in unproductive loops. The AI-First workflow gives you a repeatable process that consistently produces results. It also helps you communicate with AI more effectively, which is the core skill that determines your success.', '## Key Concepts
- Describe: Write clear, specific descriptions of what you want
- Generate: Use AI tools to produce code or applications
- Evaluate: Compare output against your requirements
- Refine: Iterate through additional prompts and adjustments
- Deploy: Push working code to production
- Rapid iteration: Complete this cycle multiple times per day

## Real-World Example
Building a customer feedback widget: You DESCRIBE it as ''a floating button that opens a feedback form with star rating and text input.'' You GENERATE it in Bolt.new. You EVALUATE and notice the button is too small on mobile. You REFINE by saying ''make the button larger on mobile screens and add a subtle animation.'' You GENERATE again and EVALUATE—now it looks great. You DEPLOY to your website. Total time: 20 minutes. Traditional development: 2-3 days.

## Practical Application
From this point forward, you will apply this workflow to every project you build in this course. You will practice writing clear descriptions, evaluating AI output critically, and refining through effective prompts. These skills transfer across all Vibe Coding tools and will remain valuable even as specific tools evolve.

## Reflection Question
Think about a recent time you tried to explain something to another person. How specific were you? Did they understand exactly what you meant? The same clarity is needed when describing projects to AI.', 4, '30 minutes', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6F8t5J2Z8XQ', '{"images":[{"title":"AI-First Development Workflow Diagram","url":"https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2016/03/26/21/13/brain-1280516_1280.png","caption":"Visual representation of the Describe, Generate, Evaluate, Refine, Deploy workflow","purpose":"Explains the AI-First development process"},{"title":"Rapid Iteration Cycle","url":"https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2017/01/10/16/30/business-1969022_1280.jpg","caption":"Diagram showing how the workflow enables rapid iteration multiple times per day","purpose":"Illustrates the rapid iteration concept"}],"video":{"title":"AI-First Development in Action","url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6F8t5J2Z8XQ","embed":true,"reason":"Watch the workflow applied to a real project"},"extra_reading":["https://docs.bolt.new - Bolt.new documentation","https://docs.lovable.dev - Lovable documentation"]}', NOW(), NOW()),
