('10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000010', '10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005', 'Real-World Agentic Workflows', 'Understanding agentic tools is one thing; integrating them effectively into real-world workflows is another. This lesson provides practical strategies for using agents in production environments.

Effective agentic workflows require clear task definition, appropriate guardrails, and systematic review processes. The goal is not to replace human judgment but to automate predictable work while maintaining quality control. The best teams use agents for high-volume, well-defined tasks while reserving human attention for architecture decisions, code review, and complex debugging.

Poorly implemented agentic workflows can create more problems than they solve—generating code that passes tests but has security vulnerabilities, introducing subtle bugs that take days to diagnose, or creating technical debt that compounds over time. Learning to use agents effectively means knowing when to trust them and when to intervene.', '## Key Concepts
- Task specification: Clear, detailed requirements reduce agent errors
- Guardrails: Automated checks that catch common issues
- Review processes: Human verification before merging agent code
- Feedback loops: Improving agent performance through corrections
- Hybrid workflows: Combining agent work with human refinement

## Real-World Example
A startup uses agentic workflows for all routine development: updating dependencies, adding CRUD endpoints, writing basic tests. Each agent-generated PR goes through automated linting and security scanning, then a quick human review focused on business logic and integration. The CTO estimates this saves 40 hours per week while maintaining code quality.

## Practical Application
