('10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000012', '10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000007', 'Prompt Engineering for Code', 'The quality of your prompts directly determines the quality of AI-generated code. This lesson teaches you specific techniques for writing prompts that produce better, more reliable software.

Prompt engineering for code differs from general prompt engineering. Code prompts need to specify technology stack, handle edge cases, define error handling, and produce consistent output formats. The best prompts are specific, structured, and provide context about the existing codebase. Vague prompts produce vague code; precise prompts produce precise code.

Poor prompting is the main reason people get frustrated with AI coding tools. They describe something vaguely, get unexpected results, and conclude the tool doesn''t work. With proper prompting techniques, the same tools produce dramatically better results. Prompt engineering is the core skill that separates effective Vibe Coders from struggling ones.', '## Key Concepts
- Specificity: Name technologies, versions, and expected behavior explicitly
- Structure: Break complex prompts into clear sections
- Context: Provide relevant code, file structure, or domain information
- Examples: Show input/output examples when possible
- Constraints: State what the code should NOT do

## Real-World Example
Bad prompt: ''Write a function to validate emails.'' Better prompt: ''Write a TypeScript function called validateEmail that takes a string input and returns {valid: boolean, error?: string}. It should check for @ symbol, valid domain format, and minimum length of 5 characters. If validation fails, return the specific error reason. Include JSDoc comments.''

## Practical Application
Take a prompt you''ve used that didn''t work well. Rewrite it using the techniques from this lesson: add specificity, structure it clearly, provide context, include examples, and state constraints. Test both versions and compare results.

## Reflection Question
Looking back at prompts you''ve written, which of the five techniques (specificity, structure, context, examples, constraints) were you missing most often?', 12, '30 minutes', '', '{"video":{"title":"Prompt Engineering for Developers","embed":true,"reason":"Advanced prompting techniques for code generation"},"extra_reading":["https://platform.openai.com/docs/guides/prompt-engineering","https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/build-with-claude/prompt-engineering"]}', NOW(), NOW()),
('10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000013', '10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000007', 'Advanced Prompting Strategies', 'Building on basic prompt engineering, this lesson covers advanced strategies for complex development scenarios: multi-step prompting, prompt chaining, iterative refinement, and working with large codebases.

Complex projects require complex prompting strategies. Multi-step prompting breaks large tasks into manageable pieces. Prompt chaining connects outputs of one prompt to inputs of another. Iterative refinement improves results through targeted follow-up prompts. Working with large codebases requires techniques for providing relevant context without exceeding token limits.

Basic prompting works for simple tasks. But real-world projects involve interdependent components, legacy code integration, and evolving requirements. Advanced strategies let you tackle projects that would be impossible with naive prompting approaches.', '## Key Concepts
- Multi-step prompting: Break large tasks into sequential prompts
- Prompt chaining: Use output of one prompt as input to next
- Iterative refinement: Improve through targeted follow-ups
- Context windowing: Provide relevant context for large codebases
- System prompts: Establish persistent context for consistent behavior

## Real-World Example
Building a complex feature: Step 1 prompt generates the data types. Step 2 uses those types to generate the API endpoint. Step 3 uses the API to generate the frontend component. Step 4 generates tests for all layers. Each step is manageable; together they build something complex.

## Practical Application
Choose a complex feature you want to build. Before prompting, plan your multi-step approach: What needs to be built first? What depends on what? Write out your prompt chain before executing it.

## Reflection Question
Think of a complex project you''ve struggled to describe in a single prompt. How would you break it into steps? What would each step need to know about previous steps?', 13, '30 minutes', '', '{"video":{"title":"Advanced Prompt Chaining Techniques","embed":true,"reason":"Real examples of complex prompt strategies"},"extra_reading":["https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/build-with-claude/prompt-engineering/chain-prompts"]}', NOW(), NOW()),
